title: EastEnders: Denise’s anguish over adoption papers revealed in new images
text:
Denise gets ready to sign the papers (Photo: PA) Share Get soaps   Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
Denise Fox hovers over the papers which would mean she signs away her child forever. 
New images from EastEnders show Denise (played by Diane Parish) looking conflicted as she gets ready to give away her child in an emotional episode airing on 2 March. 
In the pictures, Denise looks like she’s about to sign the consent forms, but doesn’t seem entirely convinced she’s doing the right thing. 
Denise gave birth to Phil Mitchell’s baby last month, but said because of their age and busy lives, they wouldn’t make good parents and agreed to put the child up for adoption. Denise is told of the family being found (Photo: BBC) Denise faces anguish over signing the adoption papers (Photo: PA) Back when Denise and Phil got smoochy and went from there... (Photo: BBC) 
Her sister Kim urged Denise to reconsider the decision, but she has no idea who the father actually is. 
The child was taken into care, and last week, viewers saw Denise being told a suitable family had been found and things would be made official. 
An EastEnders insider told the Daily Star : “Denise is in turmoil. She’s in her late 40s and doesn’t believe she can take care of her baby boy despite Kim offering her support. Kim doesn't want Denise to give up the baby (Photo: BBC) Read More EastEnders spoilers: The Square is full of (pancake) tossers and Ian's not having a happy birthday 
“Once she signs the consent form there is no going back. 
“It’s a huge decision for her and Kim is doing everything she can to try and make her change her mind. 
“Everyone will have to wait and see whether she actually goes through with the adoption.”
